{
  "texts": [
    "They integrated subword tokenization, a technique used in natural language processing that splits words into smaller units called subword tokens, to generate precise patches.",
    "Based on the LSTM network and the bidirectional recurrent neural network, Rahman et al. [592] presented BiLSTM to identify and classify the faulty code and generate possible fixes.",
    "Chen et al. [576] proposed SequenceR, a sequence-to-sequence-based deep learning system.",
    "The model adapts a copy mechanism to deal with large-scale code instances.",
    "Berabi et al. [593] proposed TFix, a pre-trained and fine-tuned language model that generates improved patches for JavaScript programs."
  ]
}